sql:
SELECT category, COUNT(dataset_id) AS dataset_count
FROM datasets
GROUP BY category;

external_knowledge:
Cumulative file size over time refers to the running total of file sizes collected within each category, year by year. This helps in understanding the data growth pattern within each category. ;
The cumulative total includes the sum of file sizes from the earliest year to the current year within the same category. For example, if a category has data in years 2010, 2011, and 2012, the cumulative file size for 2012 will be the sum of file sizes from 2010, 2011, and 2012. ;
Sorting by category and year ensures that we can observe the progression and growth of each category individually over time.

sql:
SELECT DISTINCT d.name
FROM datasets d
INNER JOIN access_logs a ON d.dataset_id = a.dataset_id;
